OverHistory.NewCommentry: Renuka Singh to Beth Mooney Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Renuka Singh bowling to Beth Mooney, short of good length ball, pitching outside leg stump, Beth Mooney plays an aggressive square drive on back foot WICKET Beth Mooney c Radha Yadav b Renuka Singh (Australia (Women) 17 Runs for 1 wickets) towards Backward Point
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
INDIA LAND AN EARLY BLOW! Renuka Singh bowling to Beth Mooney, short of good length ball, pitching outside leg stump, Beth Mooney attempts to dominate but miscues. The ball flies towards backward point, and Radha Yadav, the late call-up, proves her worth again! A spectacular diving catch, millimetres from the turf. Mooney walks without hesitation - a massive early blow for Australia!

WICKET Beth Mooney c Radha Yadav b Renuka Singh (Australia (Women) 17 Runs for 1 wickets)

WICKET! Sophie Molineux bowling to Smriti Mandhana, good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Smriti Mandhana attempts a pull but misjudges the skidding trajectory. The ball thuds into her back leg, plumb in front. A vociferous appeal erupts, but the umpire remains unmoved. McGrath, sensing opportunity, calls for the review.Tension mounts as technology takes centre stage. UltraEdge confirms no bat involvement, setting the stage for ball tracking. The crowd holds its breath. Three red lights illuminate the screen – wickets clipping, impact in line, pitching in line. Mandhana departs

OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
WICKET! Annabel Sutherland bowling to Shreyanka Patil, full length ball, pitching outside leg stump, Shreyanka Patil swings and misses. As Mooney gathers behind the stumps, Kaur, ever-alert, spots a chance for a sneaky single. But Shreyanka, mesmerized by the missed shot, is caught ball-watching.Mooney, showcasing lightning-quick thinking, sprints towards the stumps. In a flash, she whips off the bails with Shreyanka's back foot agonizingly close to the line. The stadium holds its breath as the decision goes upstairs.The third umpire meticulously examines every angle. The tension mounts with each replay. Finally, the verdict flashes on the big screen: OUT!

Shreyanka Patil run out Beth Mooney (India (Women) 141 Runs for 8 wickets)
